data.text: In sense 4 weaved is used for the past tense and past participle.
作第4义时过去式和过去分词用weaved。

data.chText: （用手或机器）编，织
data.enText: to make cloth, a carpet, a basket , etc. by crossing threads or strips across, over and under each other by hand or on a machine called a loom

data.chText: 这些篮子是用柳条编的。
data.enText: The baskets are woven from strips of willow.

data.chText: 用柳条编成篮子。
data.enText: The strips of willow are woven into baskets.

data.chText: 大多数蜘蛛可结成几乎看不见的网。
data.enText: Most spiders weave webs that are almost invisible.

data.chText: 织在一起的线
data.enText: threads woven together

data.chText: 她是纺织能手。
data.enText: She is skilled at spinning and weaving.

data.chText: （用…）编成
data.enText: to make sth by twisting flowers, pieces of wood, etc. together

data.chText: 她灵巧地把花编成了一个花环。
data.enText: She deftly wove the flowers into a garland.

data.chText: （把…）编成，编纂成，编造（故事等）
data.enText: to put facts, events, details, etc. together to make a story or a closely connected whole

data.chText: 编故事
data.enText: to weave a narrative

data.chText: 这部传记把爱因斯坦一生的各个方面编纂成书。
data.enText: The biography weaves together the various strands of Einstein's life.

data.chText: 迂回行进，穿行（以避开障碍）
data.enText: to move along by running and changing direction continuously to avoid things that are in your way

data.chText: 她在来往的车辆中穿来穿去。
data.enText: She was weaving in and out of the traffic.

data.chText: 这条路在群山中绕来绕去。
data.enText: The road weaves through a range of hills.

data.chText: 他不得不在来回乱转的人群中穿梭而行。
data.enText: He had to weave his way through the milling crowds.
weave your magic
weave a spell (over sb)

data.chText: （对某人）施展魔力；发挥（对某人的）影响力
data.enText: to perform or behave in a way that is attractive or interesting, or that makes sb behave in a particular way

data.chText: 亨利星期三能施展魔力击败意大利队吗？
data.enText: Will Henry be able to weave his magic against Italy on Wednesday?

tr: pattern of weaving or structure of a fabric
interlace by or as if by weaving
create a piece of cloth by interlacing strands of fabric, such as wool or cotton
to move or cause to move in a sinuous, spiral, or circular course
example: the river winds through the hills
the path meanders through the vineyards
sometimes, the gout wanders through the entire body

value.boxr_value: The form weaved is used for the past tense and past participle for meaning 4. 义项4的过去式和过去分词为 weaved。

value.def: If you weave cloth or a carpet, you make it by crossing threads over and under each other using a frame or machine called a loom.

example.ex: They would spin and weave cloth, cook and attend to the domestic side of life...
example.tran: 她们纺纱、织布、煮饭以及料理家务。

example.ex: In one room, young mothers weave while babies doze in their laps.
example.tran: 在一间屋子里，年轻的母亲们在织布，而她们的孩子就在她们膝上打盹。

example.ex: When I studied weaving, I became intrigued with natural dyes.
example.tran: 学习纺织激起了我对天然染料的兴趣。

value.def: A particular weave is the way in which the threads are arranged in a cloth or carpet.

example.ex: Fabrics with a close weave are ideal for painting.
example.tran: 编织紧密的布最适合作画。

value.def: If you weave something such as a basket, you make it by crossing long plant stems or fibres over and under each other.

example.ex: Jenny weaves baskets from willow she grows herself.
example.tran: 珍妮用她自己种的柳树的枝条编篮子。

example.ex: The floors are covered with woven straw mats.
example.tran: 地板上铺着编织的草垫。

value.def: If you weave your way somewhere, you move between and around things as you go there.

example.ex: The cars then weaved in and out of traffic at top speed...
example.tran: 这些轿车就在车流中全速穿行。

example.ex: He weaved around the tables to where she sat with Bob...
example.tran: 他绕过一张张桌子，走到她和鲍勃坐着的地方。

example.ex: He weaves his way through a crowd.

value.def: If you weave a story, you invent a complicated story.

example.ex: Jan Roberts weaves a compelling tale which traps a young woman in a world run by the Mafia.
example.tran: 简·罗伯茨编了一个引人入胜的故事，诱骗一位年轻女性进入了黑手党的地盘。

value.def: If you weave details into a story or design, you include them, so that they are closely linked together or become an important part of the story or design.

example.ex: She weaves imaginative elements into her poems...
example.tran: 她在诗中编织着奇思妙想。

example.ex: Bragg weaves together the histories of his main characters.
example.tran: 布拉格把他主要人物的身世都串在一起。

value.tran: 将(素材等)编入（故事或设计中）
